<br>
In order to get Despondo to talk to you, you need help from an Enchanter, Bard, or Druid. The trick is Harmony (Pacification, or Silent Song of Quellious depending on whether you have a bard, ench, or druid helping you.). Harmony all the NPC's in Despondo's building. Go inside, staying invisible, and get close to despondo, but not on top of him. You'll need to be close enough to hand him items, but not so close that he or one of his friends will attack you when you drop invis.<br>
<br>
When you are in position, kill invis, and hand him the gems for the bottles. DO NOT CLICK TRADE YET! Have your friend invis you with the trade window open. He is now indifferent to you-Click trade. Voila-you just started the quest and skipped the 100's of hours of faction work required to do the quest. Use the same process when you finish the quest, handing in the 3 bottles.<br>
<br>
I learned this months ago, but held back on posting it out of fear that it would be nerfed. But now I'm reading posts indicating that people are in a bind and need to do the quest, so I figured I'd give up the information.<br>
<br>
This worked months ago for me, but who knows-Maybe it's been patched now? Give it a shot and let me know how it turns out.<br>
<br>
Take care,<br>
<br>
Peaceful Salvation <p>“In the time of my favor I heard you, <br>
